  <prompt>
    Create a new developer guide at `docs/guides/EMAIL-COMPOSER-COMPONENT-GUIDE.md` documenting the canonical `<EmailComposer />` engine and its 3 wrappers (`<SendEmailStep />`, `<SendEmailDialog />`, `<SendEmailPage />`) for Spaarke developers building new email-touching surfaces.

    The guide is the practical "how do I use this" reference for every future surface — it must accurately reflect what shipped in Waves 1–5 (engine API, wrapper prop surfaces, validation contract, error handling, attachment sources, mount variants). It also tells developers what NOT to do (per ADR-033 MUST NOT rules: no 6th send-email implementation, no inline `fetch`, no `@spaarke/auth` import in shared lib).
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Spaarke shared-lib documentation author. Familiar with the EmailComposer engine + wrappers as built in Waves 1–5 and the ADR-033 canonical pattern.
  </role>

  <goal>
    A complete, accurate developer guide at `docs/guides/EMAIL-COMPOSER-COMPONENT-GUIDE.md` covering: when to use which wrapper (decision tree), prop API for each wrapper, mount variants per NFR-03 (page/dialog/inline), validation contract per FR-08 (canonical error codes), error handling via `SendCommunicationError` per FR-09, attachment sources per FR-07 (4 sources), mode logic per FR-10–FR-13 (5 modes), and explicit ADR-033 references. Cross-linked from `docs/guides/SHARED-UI-COMPONENTS-GUIDE.md` (task 089 adds the back-reference).
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per FR-27 #2, a new developer guide is required. The guide is the practical companion to ADR-033 (which is architectural) — it covers actual usage patterns with code examples.

      Surfaces consuming `<EmailComposer />` family today: 5 create-record wizards (via SendEmailStep), FilePreview (via SendEmailDialog), Code Page (via SendEmailPage), DocumentEmailWizard (via SendEmailStep), SummarizeFiles (via SendEmailStep). The guide documents the same usage pattern these consumers established in Waves 3–5.
    </background>
