    <step order="5">Draft the guide with sections:
      (a) Overview + ADR-033 reference
      (b) When to use which wrapper (decision tree: wizard-step → SendEmailStep; dialog → SendEmailDialog; standalone page → SendEmailPage; programmatic no-UI → sendCommunication())
      (c) `<SendEmailStep />` prop API (wizard step usage)
      (d) `<SendEmailDialog />` prop API (popup dialog usage)
      (e) `<SendEmailPage />` prop API (Code Page usage)
      (f) Mount variants (page/dialog/inline) per NFR-03 — visual differences
      (g) Validation contract (canonical error codes per FR-08)
      (h) Error handling (`SendCommunicationError` per FR-09)
      (i) Attachment sources (4 sources per FR-07)
      (j) Mode logic (compose/view/reply/forward/draft per FR-10–FR-13)
      (k) ADR-033 MUST NOT rules (do not add a 6th implementation; do not inline `fetch`; do not import `@spaarke/auth` in shared lib)
      (l) Code examples for the 3 most common patterns (wizard step, dialog launch, Code Page mount)
      (m) Related docs (ADR-033, SHARED-UI-COMPONENTS-GUIDE, communication-service-architecture, COMMUNICATION-ATTACHMENT-POLICY)
    </step>
    <step order="6">Verify code examples compile against the as-built engine API (read EmailComposer.tsx imports + component signature).</step>
    <step order="7">Add cross-reference from `docs/guides/SHARED-UI-COMPONENTS-GUIDE.md` to the new guide (task 089 does this, but include the planned link in the new guide's "Related docs" section as well).</step>
    <step order="8">Run `grep` for orphaned references that might benefit from a cross-link to the new guide.</step>
